block company
  .policy
    em.updating-date Updated October 15, 2013.
    
    p.bold
      | We are committed to protecting your privacy. Authorized employees within the company on a need to know basis only use any information collected from individual users. We constantly review our systems and data to ensure the best possible service to our users.
    p
      | We collect the e-mail addresses of those who communicate with us via e-mail, aggregate information on what pages consumers access or visit, and information volunteered by the consumer (such as survey information and/or site registrations). The information we collect is used to improve the content of our Web pages and the quality of our service.
    
    h2 A. INFORMATION GATHERING AND USAGE.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 1
      | . When you register for Waaave we ask for information such as your name, email address, location information and skills.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 2
      | . Waaave uses collected information for the following general purposes: identification and authentication, services improvement, contact, and research.
    
    h2 B. COOKIES.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 1
      | . A cookie is a small amount of data, which often includes an anonymous unique identifier, that is sent to your browser from a web site's computers and stored on your computer's hard drive.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 2
      | . Cookies are required to use the Waaave service.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 3
      | . We use cookies to record current session information. You are required to re-login to your Waaave account after a certain period of time has elapsed to protect you against others accidentally accessing your account contents.
    
    h2 C. DATA STORAGE.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 1
      | . Waaave uses third party vendors and hosting partners to provide the necessary hardware, software, networking, storage, and related technology required to run Waaave. Although Waaave owns the code, databases, and all rights to the Waaave application, you retain all rights to your data.
    
    h2 D. DISCLOSURE.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 1
      | . Waaave may disclose personally identifiable information under special circumstances, such as to comply with subpoenas or when your actions violate the Terms of Service.
    
    h2 E. CHANGES.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 1
      | . Waaave may periodically update this policy. We will notify you about significant changes in the way we treat personal information by sending a notice to the primary email address specified in your Waaave primary account holder account or by placing a prominent notice on our site.
    
    p.item
      span.bold 2
      | . Any questions about this Privacy Policy should be addressed through 
      a(href='{% url "company.views.contact" %}') our contact form
      | .
